# Logs
logs/
*.log

# SWARM task worktrees (ai/ARCHITECTURE.md "Worktree lifecycle")
.swarm-workspaces/

# Project skills (Claude/Antigravity/Codex) are local-only tooling, not committed —
# see ai/RULES.md §4. Ignores the canonical .claude/skills/<name>/SKILL.md copies and
# the .agents/skills/<name> symlinks that expose them to Antigravity and Codex.
.claude/skills/
.agents/skills/

# SWARM agent hand-off/scratch artifacts (src/scm/delivery.ts's `HANDOFF_FILENAMES`,
# `PROGRESS_FILENAME`, and delegation scratch) — written at the worktree root by a
# phase's agent, read by deterministic delivery, and never meant to be committed;
# `commitPreparedTree` already excludes them from its own `git add`, but they were
# not previously gitignored, which let an unrelated commit accidentally track two
# of them (fixed alongside issue #241). Keeping them ignored here is the durable
# backstop against that recurring.
implementation_handoff.json
review_handoff.json
respond_to_review_handoff.json
respond_to_ci_handoff.json
resolve_conflicts_handoff.json
.swarm_delivery.json
.swarm-delegation-*
